{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d7df6afda2c50e8d35", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70bd9948bc1b21da2b1f"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6ebaa"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "112", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "Analysis shows that nickel oxide consists of nickel ion with 96% ions having <math><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup></math> configuration and 4% having <math><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup></math> configuration. Which amongst the following best represents the formula of the oxide?", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "2esye", "text": "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1.02</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1.00</mn></mrow></msub></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "OUpmO", "text": "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0.96</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1.00</mn></mrow></msub></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "pVoNj", "text": "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0.98</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0.98</mn></mrow></msub></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "a932f", "text": "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0.98</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1.00</mn></mrow></msub></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mn>4</mn><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> (Atomic number = 28)<br />So <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup></math> and <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup></math><br />Hence, 96% ion of <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math> and 4% ions of <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math> are present.<br />Let number of <math><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math> ion present in the crystal = x<br />Using electroneutrality rule,<br />Total positive charge = Total negative charge<br /><math><mn>96</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>3</mn